Subject: streptogramin vgb lyase

Subject: streptogramin vat acetyltransferase

Subject: myrA
Value: myrA is a methyltransferase found in Micromonospora griseorubida and confers resistance to mycinamicin, tylosin and lincosamides. Specifically, this enzyme adds a methyl group to guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering) of 23S ribosomal RNA. MyrA is found in the mycinamicin biosynthetic cluster and is one mechanism by which M. griseorubida protects itself from self-destruction when producing this macrolide.

Subject: Mycobacterium tuberculosis katG mutations conferring resistance to isoniazid
Value: katG is a catalase-peroxidase that catalyzes the activation of isoniazid. Isoniazid inhibits mycolic acid synthesis, which prevents cell wall synthesis in mycobacteria. Mutations in katG results in inability to activate isoniazid. Over 280 different mutations have been documented in PubMed for katG, with mutations to Ser315 being the most prevalent.

Subject: Mycobacterium tuberculosis inhA mutations conferring resistance to isoniazid
Value: inhA is a enoyl-acyl carrier reductase used in lipid metabolism and farry acid biosynthesis. It is inhibited by isoniazid. mutations in the promoter region or multiple copies of the inhA shows marked resistance to isoniazid mediated inhibition of mycolic acid biosynthesis.

Subject: Mycobacterium tuberculosis pncA mutations conferring resistance to pyrazinamide
Value: pncA is a pyrazinamidase/nicotinamidase. It catalyzes the activation of pyrazinamide. Some mutation within pncA are associated with loss of enzyme activity, resulting in pyrazinamide resistance.

Subject: antibiotic resistant inhA
Value: inhA is a enoyl-acyl carrier reductase used in lipid metabolism and fatty acid biosynthesis. It is inhibited by isoniazid. Mutations in the promoter region or multiple copies of the inhA shows marked resistance to isoniazid mediated inhibition of mycolic acid biosynthesis.

Subject: pyrazinamide resistant pncA
Value: pncA is a pyrazinamidase/nicotinamidase. It catalyzes the activation of pyrazinamide to pyrazinoic acid. Mutations arise within the pncA gene that caused the loss of pyrazinamidase activity is the major mechanism of antibiotic resistance

Subject: antibiotic resistant pgsA

Subject: antibiotic sensitive inhA

Subject: Antibiotic resistant iniA

Subject: Antibiotic resistant iniC
Value: iniC, an isoniazid-induced protein, is part of the iniBAC operon that participates in the development of tolerance to both isoniazid and ethambutol. May function through a MDR-pump like mechanism, although it does not appear to directly transport isoniazid from the cell

Subject: antibiotic resistant ndh
Value: ndh is a NADH oxidase. It participates in antibiotic resistance by diminishing NADH oxidation and consequently causes an increase in NADH concentration and depletion of NAD+. This alteration of the NADH/NAD+ ratio prevents the peroxidation reactions required for the activation of INH, as well as the displacement of the NADH-isonicotinic acyl complex from InhA enzyme binding site.

Subject: antibiotic resistant kasA

Subject: antibiotic sensitive embR

Subject: antibiotic sensitive kasA
Value: kasA is a ketoacyl acyl carrier protein synthase that catalyzes the condensation reaction of fatty acid synthesis by the addition to an acyl acceptor of two carbons from malonyl-ACP. It is involved in elongation of fatty acids intermediate in the biosynthetic pathway of mycolic acids.

Subject: Escherichia coli nfsA mutations conferring resistance to nitrofurantoin
Value: nfsA encodes the major oxygen-insesitive nitroreductase in E. coli. The first step of resistance to nitrofurazone is mutation of nfsA.

Subject: antibiotic resistant nfsB
Value: nsfB encodes a minor oxygen-insensitive nitroreductase. NfsB reduces a broad range of nitroaromatic compounds including the antibiotics nitrofurazone and nitrofurantoin. NfsB is a flavin mononucleotide (FMN)-containing protein and uses both NADH and NADPH as a source of reducing equivalents. Mutations in nfsB lead to increased resistance to nitrofurazone and furazolidone in an nfsA mutant background.

Subject: Escherichia coli nfsB with mutation conferring resistance to nitrofurantoin
Value: nfsB encodes the minor oxygen-insesitive nitroreductase in E. coli. The first step of resistance to nitrofurazone is mutation of nfsA, while the increased resistance associated with second step mutants is a consequence of nfsB mutation.

Subject: Enterococcus faecalis cls with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin

Subject: eatAv

Subject: lnuE
Value: lnuE encodes a lincosamide resistance gene isolated from Streptococcus suis that was truncated by an ISEnfa5-cfr-ISEnfa5 segment insertion. It shares the closest sequence similarity to lnuA.

Subject: mphM

Subject: Escherichia coli murA with mutation conferring resistance to fosfomycin
Value: murA or UDP-N-acetylglucosamine enolpyruvyl transferase catalyses the initial step in peptidoglycan biosynthesis and is inhibited by fosfomycin. Overexpression of murA through mutations such as Asp369Asn and Leu370Ile confers fosfomycin resistance. Extensive evidence has shown the significance of C115 mutations in conferring fosfomycin resistance since this residue represents a primary binding site for the antibiotic across many species.

Subject: Staphylococcus aureus murA with mutation conferring resistance to fosfomycin
Value: murA or UDP-N-acetylglucosamine enolpyruvyl transferase catalyses the initial step in peptidoglycan biosynthesis and is inhibited by fosfomycin. Overexpression of murA through mutations confers fosfomycin resistance.

Subject: Borreliella burgdorferi murA with mutation conferring resistance to fosfomycin
Value: murA or UDP-N-acetylglucosamine enolpyruvyl transferase catalyses the initial step in peptidoglycan biosynthesis and is inhibited by fosfomycin. Mutations to the murA enzyme confers resistance to the antibiotic.

Subject: Enterococcus faecium liaF mutant conferring daptomycin resistance
Value: liaF is an accessory protein that acts as a negative regulator of liaRS signal transduction pathway. Mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

Subject: Enterococcus faecalis liaS mutant conferring daptomycin resistance
Value: liaS is a histidine kinase found in the liaFSR signal transduction pathway. Mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

Subject: Enterococcus faecalis liaR mutant conferring daptomycin resistance
Value: liaR is a response regulator found in the liaFSR signal transduction pathway. Mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

Subject: Staphylococcus aureus walK with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin
Value: walK is the histidine kinase sensor of a two-component regulatory system controlling peptidoglycan metabolism through regulation of the expression of most of the peptidoglycan hydrolase genes. Mutations in the gene have been found that confer daptomycin resistance.

Subject: Enterococcus faecalis gdpD with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance
Value: gdpD is a glycerolphosphodiesterase whose mutations confer resistance to daptomycin.

Subject: Staphylococcus aureus agrA with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin
Value: agrA is an autoinducer in a peptide-quorum two-component regulatory system whose mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

Subject: Enterococcus faecalis gshF with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance
Value: gshF is a bifunctional glutamate-cysteine ligase/ glutathione synthetase that when mutated, confers daptomycin resistance.

Subject: carO
Value: carO is a transmembrane beta-barrel involved in the influx of carbapenem antibiotics in Acinetobacter baumannii. Disruption of the carO gene by distinct insertion elements results in a loss of carO expression causing resistance to carbapenem antibiotics. Homologs of carO have been identified in genera Acinetobacter, Moraxella and Psychrobacter.

Subject: Enterococcus faecalis drmA with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance
Value: drmA is an uncharacterized 6-pass membrane protein, with mutations to the protein causing modest resistance to daptomycin.

Subject: mgrB
Value: mgrB is a small transmembrane protein produced in the PhoPQ signalling system. It acts as a negative regulator in this system. Inactivation or down-regulation of mgrB confers colistin resistance by absence as shown in Klebsiella pneumoniae

Subject: aminocoumarin resistant alaS
Value: alanyl-tRNA synthetase conferring resistance to novobiocin in Escherichia coli

Subject: qacH
Value: qacH is a subunit of the qac multidrug efflux pump in Staphylococcus saprophyticus

Subject: kdpE
Value: kdpE is a transcriptional activator that is part of the two-component system KdpD/KdpE that is studied for its regulatory role in potassium transport and has been identified as an adaptive regulator involved in the virulence and intracellular survival of pathogenic bacteria. kdpE regulates a range of virulence loci through direct promoter binding.

Subject: leuO
Value: leuO, a LysR family transcription factor, exists in a wide variety of bacteria of the family Enterobacteriaceae and is involved in the regulation of as yet unidentified genes affecting the stress response and pathogenesis expression. LeuO is also an activator of the MdtNOP efflux pump.

Subject: mfd
Value: mfd dissociates transcription elongation complexes blocked at nonpairing lesions and mediates recruitment of DNA repair proteins. The Mfd (mutation frequency decline) protein, also known as transcription-repair coupling factor, is responsible for ATP-dependent removal of stalled RNA polymerase from DNA lesions by inducing forward movement of the RNA polymerase and subsequent recruitment of nucleotide excision repair machinery to the sites of the lesions.

Subject: Escherichia coli UhpA with mutation conferring resistance to fosfomycin
Value: uhpA is a positive activator of the fosfomycin importer uhpT, thus mutations to uhpA confer fosfomycin resistance by reducing uhpT expression. Both knockout and amino acid substitution mutations have been found that confer resistance, with the Protein Knockout model describing the large, knockout mutations causing loss of function of the gene, and the Protein Variant model describing the amino acid substitutions.

Subject: Staphylococcus aureus menA with mutation conferring resistance to lysocin
Value: menA encodes a 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoate octaprenyltransferase, with mutations to the protein conferring resistance to lysocin E.

Subject: oqxAB
Value: oqxAB encodes for OqxAB, a plasmid-encoded efflux pump, which confer resistance to multiple agents including fluoroquinolones.

Subject: ceftolozane
Value: a 5th generation cephalosporin antibiotic

Subject: rpsJ
Value: rpsJ is a tetracycline resistance protein identified in Neisseria gonorrhoeae. Tetracycline resistance is conferred by binding to the ribosome as a 30S ribosomal protection protein.

Subject: omadacycline
Value: a aminomethylcycline antibiotic that targets 16s rRNA in gram positive and gram negative bacteria

Subject: efrA
Value: efrA is a part of the EfrAB efflux pump, and both efrA and efrB are necessary to confer drug resistance.

Subject: efrB
Value: efrB is a part of the EfrAB efflux pump, and both efrA and efrB are necessary to confer multidrug resistance.

Subject: microcin J25
Value: microcin J25 is a peptide antibiotic that inhibits transcription by bacterial RNA polymerase. MccJ25 is produced by Escherichia coli strains that harbor a plasmid-borne antibiotic-synthesis and antibiotic-export cassette, consisting of a gene for MccJ25 precursor (a 58 residue linear peptide), two genes for factors that process MccJ25 precursor into MccJ25, and one gene for export of MccJ25.

Subject: hmrM
Value: hmrM is a multidrug efflux pump belonging to the MATE family and functions as a  Na+/drug antiporter.

Subject: efmA
Value: efmA is an MFS transporter permease in  E. faecium.

Subject: efpA
Value: efpA is an MFS transporter found in Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

Subject: farAB
Value: farAB is an MFS efflux pump found in gonococci that is involved in antibacterial fatty acid resistance. Moreover, expression of the tandemly linked farA and farB genes was positively associated with the presence of the MtrR transcriptional regulatory protein that normally downregulates the expression of mtrCDE.

Subject: farA
Value: farA is the membrane fusion protein that is part of the farAB efflux pump.

Subject: farB
Value: farB is the cytoplasmic transporter protein that is part of the farAB efflux pump. farB corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.

Subject: hp1181
Value: hp1181 is a translocase that is part of the MFS efflux pump family. It is found in H. pylori and has role in the active efflux of antibiotics.

Subject: hp1184
Value: hp1184 is a translocase that belongs to the MATE efflux pump family. It is found in H. pylori and is involved in the active efflux of antibiotics.

Subject: lfrA
Value: lfrA is involved in the active efflux of quinolones and is found in Mycobacteroides abscessus.

Subject: lmrP
Value: lmrP is a proton motive force-dependent drug transporter that is part of the MFS efflux pump family.

Subject: mphI
Value: mphI is a macrolide phosphotransferase protein found in Paenibacillus sp. LC231, a strain of Paenibacillus isolated from Lechuguilla Cave, NM, USA. Confers resistance to macrolide antibiotics. Described by Pawlowski et al. 2016.

Subject: rphB
Value: rphB is a rifampin phosphotransferase protein found in Paenibacillus sp. LC231, a strain of Paenibacillus isolated from Lechuguilla Cave, NM, USA. Confers resistance to rifamycin antibiotics, specifically rifampin, through rifampin inactivation. Described by Pawlowski et al. 2016.

Subject: cpaA
Value: cpaA is a capreomycin acetyltransferase protein found in Paenibacillus sp. LC231, an isolated strain of Paenibacillus in Lechuguilla Cave, NM, USA. Confers resistance to capreomycin, an aminoglycoside antibiotic. Described by Pawlowski et al. 2016.

Subject: para-aminosalicylic acid
Value: para-aminosalicylic acid (PAS) is an anti-tubercular antibiotic agent, often used in conjunction with Isoniazid for treatment of M. tuberculosis infections. PAS diminishes bacterial cell growth by limiting folic acid production.

Subject: tetAB(46)
Value: tetAB(46) is a heterodimeric ABC transporter conferring tetracycline resistance in Streptococcus australis isolated from the oral cavity. Both tetA(46) and tetB(46) genes are required for resistance.

Subject: tetA(46)
Value: tetA(46) is a subunit of tetAB(46), a heterodimeric ABC transporter, that is required for conferring tetracycline resistance in Streptococcus australis isolated from the oral cavity.

Subject: tetB(46)
Value: tetB(46) is a subunit of tetAB(46), a heterodimeric ABC transporter, that is required for conferring tetracycline resistance in Streptococcus australis isolated from the oral cavity.

Subject: tetAB(60)
Value: tetAB(60) is an ABC transporter that confers resistance to tetracycline and tigercycline identified by screening a human saliva metagenomic library in Escherichia coli. Both tetA(60) and tetB(60) are required for resistance.

Subject: tetA(60)
Value: tetA(60) is a subunit of tetAB(60), an ABC transporter that confers resistance to tetracycline and tigercycline identified by screening a human saliva metagenomic library in Escherichia coli, which is required for resistance.

Subject: tetB(60)
Value: tetB(60) is a subunit of tetAB(60), an ABC transporter that confers resistance to tetracycline and tigercycline identified by screening a human saliva metagenomic library in Escherichia coli, which is required for resistance.

Subject: antibiotic sensitive fabI
Value: fabI is a bacterial enoyl-acyl carrier reductase (ENR) isozyme. As with other ENRs, mutations in fabI can confer resistance to the biocide triclosan.

Subject: Escherichia coli fabI mutations conferring resistance to isoniazid and triclosan
Value: fabI is a enoyl-acyl carrier reductase used in lipid metabolism and fatty acid biosynthesis. The bacterial biocide Triclosan blocks the final reduction step in fatty acid elongation, inhibiting biosynthesis. Point mutations in fabI can confer resistance to Triclosan and Isoniazid

Subject: kdpDE
Value: kdpDE is a two-component regulatory system in Escherichia coli, well studied for its role in potassium transport and homeostasis. kdpE is also implicated in virulence loci regulation and overexpression of kdpE is shown to confer resistance to aminoglycoside antibiotics.

Subject: kdpD
Value: kdpD is a component of the two-component regulatory system, kdpDE. This system is involved in potassium transport and homeostasis, and has been implicated in virulence factor regulation along with kdpE.

Subject: Escherichia coli fabG mutations conferring resistance to triclosan
Value: fabG is a 3-oxoacyl-acyl carrier protein reductase involved in lipid metabolism and fatty acid biosynthesis.The bacterial biocide Triclosan blocks the final reduction step in fatty acid elongation, inhibiting biosynthesis. Point mutations in fabG can confer resistance to Triclosan.

Subject: antibiotic sensitive fabG
Value: fabG is a bacterial 3-oxoacyl enoyl-acyl carrier reductase (ENR) isozyme. As with other ENRs, mutations in fabG are shown to confer resistance to the biocide triclosan.

Subject: lnuG
Value: lnuG is a transposon-mediated lincosamide nucleotidyltransferase found in Enterococcus faecalis on Tn6260.

Subject: Enterobacter cloacae rob
Value: rob is a positive regulator for the acrAB efflux genes, and is structurally similar to SoxS and MarA.

Subject: Escherichia coli rob
Value: rob is a positive regulator for the acrAB efflux genes, and is structurally similar to SoxS and MarA.

Subject: FosA6
Value: fosA6 is a plasmid-encoded enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Escherichia coli by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule.

Subject: FosA7
Value: fosA7 is an enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Escherichia coli by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule.

Subject: Antibiotic resistant iniB
Value: iniB, an isoniazid-induced protein, is part of the iniBAC operon that participates in the development of tolerance to both isoniazid and ethambutol. May function through a MDR-pump like mechanism, although it does not appear to directly transport isoniazid from the cell.

Subject: Mycobacterium tuberculosis ribD with mutation conferring resistance to para-aminosalicylic acid
Value: ribD is a Mycobacterium tuberculosis riboflavin biosynthesis enzyme. Point mutations in ribD cause enzyme overexpression, which allows the C-terminal reductase domain to act as an alternative dihydrofolate reductase. Thus, mutations in ribD confer resistance to DHFR inhibitors such as para-aminosalicylic acid.

Subject: mecD
Value: mecD is a PBP2a variant identified on a genomic resistance island in Macrococcus caseolyticus. MecD confers resistance to methicillin and other beta-lactam antibiotics through the production of an alternative low-affinity PBP. First described by Schwendener et al. 2017 and identified from canine and bovine sources.

Subject: cepA beta-lactamase
Value: cepA beta-lactamases are Class A beta-lactamases found in Bateroides fragilis and have the ability to hydrolyze cephalosporin.

Subject: NmcA beta-lactamase
Value: nmcA beta-lactamases are chromosomal-encoded Class A beta-lactamases first isolated from Enterobacter cloacae, specifically a clinical strain known as NOR-1. nmcA beta-lactamases have been shown to hydrolyze carbapenems.

Subject: blaZ beta-lactamase
Value: blaZ beta-lactamases are Class A beta-lactamases. These beta-lactamases are responsible for penicillin resistance in Staphylococcus aureus.

Subject: vanUG
Value: vanUG is a vanG variant found in the vanG gene cluster.

Subject: vanVB
Value: vanVB is a vanV variant found in the vanB gene cluster. It is found in some but not all vanB operons in E. faecalis, suggesting the existence of varied gene compositions in vanB operons.

Subject: vanJ membrane protein
Value: vanJ and vanJ homologue proteins confer resistance to the teicoplanin.

Subject: antibiotic resistant fabI
Value: fabI is a enoyl-acyl carrier reductase used in lipid metabolism and fatty acid biosynthesis. The bacterial biocide Triclosan blocks the final reduction step in fatty acid elongation, inhibiting biosynthesis. Point mutations in fabI can confer resistance to Triclosan and Isoniazid.

Subject: antibiotic resistant fabG
Value: fabG is a 3-oxoacyl-acyl carrier protein reductase involved in lipid metabolism and fatty acid biosynthesis. The bacterial biocide Triclosan blocks the final reduction step in fatty acid elongation, inhibiting biosynthesis. Point mutations in fabG can confer resistance to Triclosan.

Subject: subclass B1 Vibrio cholerae varG beta-lactamase
Value: varG is an Ambler class B metallo-beta-lactamase found on the antibiotic resistance var regulon in Vibrio cholerae, along with an antibiotic efflux pump varABCDEF. These genes are organized as a regulon under the control of VarR transcriptional activator. VarG was shown to have beta-lactamase activity against penicillins, carbapenems and cephalosporins in-vitro.

Subject: Vibrio cholerae varG
Value: varG is an Ambler class B metallo-beta-lactamase found on the antibiotic resistance var regulon in Vibrio cholerae, along with an antibiotic efflux pump varABCDEF. These genes are organized as a regulon under the control of VarR transcriptional activator. VarG was shown to have beta-lactamase activity against penicillins, carbapenems and cephalosporins in-vitro. Described by Lin HV et al. 2017.

Subject: sul4
Value: sul4 is a dihydropteroate synthase gene and mobile sulfonamide resistance gene shown to confer resistance when expressed in E. coli.

Subject: MIC unit
Value: mg/L

Subject: tet(W/N/W)
Value: tet(W/N/W) is a mosaic tetracycline resistance gene and ribosomal protection protein.

Subject: msr-type ABC-F protein
Value: msr-type ABC-F subfamily ribosomal protection proteins expression in Staphylococci species and confer resistance to erythromycin and streptogramin B antibiotics through antibiotic target protection mechanisms.

Subject: vmlR
Value: vmlR is an ABC-F ATPase ribosomal protection protein identified in Bacillus subtilus. Shown to confer resistance to lincomycin and streptogramin A virginiamycin. Described by Crowe-McAuliffe et al. 2018.

Subject: murG transferase
Value: murG acetylglucosaminyltransferase enzymes inhibited by vancomycin. Mutations in murG confer resistance to vancomycin through antibiotic target alteration.

Subject: erm(32)
Value: erm(32) is a rRNA methyltransferase. Encodes methyltransferases that modify 23S rRNA.

Subject: erm(46)
Value: erm(46) is transferable determinant that confers resistance to macrolides.

Subject: clcD
Value: clcD gene can provide resistance to representatives of five of the six antibiotic groups previously shown to be affected by Cfr.  clcD was originally found in Clostridioides difficile and is cfr-like.

Subject: ermZ
Value: ermZ is an methyltransferase modifying 23S rRNA conferring resistance to Spiramycin.

Subject: erm(40)
Value: erm(40) is an adenine RNA methylase and confers intrinsic resistance in Mycobacteria.

Subject: EreD
Value: erythromycin esterase protein

Subject: qnrE1
Value: qnrE1 is a member of the qnrE family of plasmid-borne (fluoro)quinolone-resistance genes, with chromosomal origins from Enterobacter spp.

Subject: qnrE2
Value: qnrE2 is a qnrE-member of plasmid-borne (fluoro)quinolone-resistance genes.

Subject: Corynebacterium striatum tetA
Value: tetAB genes of the Corynebacterium striatum R-plasmid which encode an ABC transporter and confer tetracycline, oxytetracycline, and oxalic resistance

Subject: aacA43
Value: aacA43 is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by integrons found in Klebsiella pneumoniae, Escherichia coli, and Enterobacter cloaecae

Subject: Erm(K)
Value: 23S rRNA (adenine(2058)-N(6))-methyltransferase Erm(K) [Bacillus halodurans]

Subject: dfrA6 from Proteus mirabilis
Value: dfrA6 is a dihydrofolate reductase that confers resistance to trimethoprim.

Subject: dfrI
Value: dfrI is a dihydrofolate reductase that is resistant to trimethoprim.

Subject: cfr(B)
Value: cfr(B) has been observed in mobile genetic elements in E. faecium and Clostridioides difficile and confers resistance to linezolid, clindamycin, erythromycin, chloramphenicol, and retapamulin.

Subject: catII from Escherichia coli K-12
Value: catII is a chloramphenicol acetyltransferase. This particular catII is found in E.coli K-12. Confers resistance to chloramphenicol.

Subject: catA4
Value: catA4 is a chloramphenicol acetyltransferase that confers resistance to chloramphenicol.

Subject: catA8
Value: catA8 is a chloramphenicol acetyltransferase that confers resistance to chloramphenicol.

Subject: catB11
Value: catB11 is a chloramphenicol acetyltransferase that confers resistance to chloramphenicol.

Subject: cmlA8
Value: cmlA8 is a plasmid that confers resistance to chloramphenicol.

Subject: pexA
Value: pexA is a florfenicol and chloramphenicol resistance gene discovered in Alaskan soil.

Subject: rmtE2
Value: 16S rRNA mathyltransferase gene with a single nucleotide mutation compared to rmtE.

Subject: aadS
Value: a novel Tn4551 streptomycin-resistance gene that was phenotypically silent in wild-type Bacteroides; expression could be activated by a trans-acting chromosomal mutation

Subject: aadA10
Value: aadA10 is a aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids in P. aeruginosa.

Subject: aadA8b
Value: aadA8b is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids in E. coli; can be created by a recombination event  between aadA1 and aadA2

Subject: vga(E) Staphylococcus cohnii
Value: vga(E) gene variant that confers resistance to pleuromutilins, lincosamides and streptogramin A antibiotics in staphylococci

Subject: Mycobacterium tuberculosis inhA mutations conferring resistance to ethionamide
Value: inhA is a enoyl-acyl carrier reductase used in lipid metabolism and farry acid biosynthesis. It is inhibited by ethionamide. Mutations in the promoter region or multiple copies of the inhA show marked resistance to ethionamide mediated inhibition of mycolic acid biosynthesis.

Subject: pyrazinamide resistant clpC1
Value: clpC1 is a subunit of the clp protease that is ATP-dependent. It functions to direct the clp protease to specific substrates. In the presence of ATP it hydrolyses proteins and may be involved in the degradation of denatured proteins.

Subject: pyrazinamide resistant gpsI
Value: gpsI codes for polyribonucleotide nucleotidyltransferase which is a protein involved in mRNA degradation. It catalyzes the phosphorolysis of single-stranded polyribonucleotides in the 3'- to 5'-direction.

Subject: pyrazinamide resistant ppsC
Value: ppsC codes for the phthiocerol synthesis polyketide synthase type 1. It is involved in the elongation of C22-24 fatty acids by the addition of methylmalonyl-CoA extender units to yield phthiocerol derivatives in a complete reduction. Research has pointed towards this protein to be a high confidence drug target.

Subject: pyrazinamide resistant ppsD
Value: ppsD codes for the phthiocerol synthesis polyketide synthase type 1. It is involved in the elongation of C22-24 fatty acids by the addition of malonyl-CoA extender units to yield phthiocerol derivatives in a partial reduction.

Subject: Ethionamide resistant fabG1
Value: fabG1 is involved in the fatty acid synthesis pathway, acting in the first reduction step for mycolic acid. It is associated with ethionamide resistance.

Subject: ethionamide resistant nudC
Value: nudC is a NADH pyrophosphatase that is involved in nicotinate and nicotinamide metabolism. Mutations that occur on the nudC gene resulting in the inability for ethionamide to function.

Subject: isoniazid resistant ahpC
Value: an alkyl hydroperoxide reductase that catalyzes the reduction of organic hydrogen peroxide to water and organic alcohols. Plays a role in protecting oxidative stress.

Subject: isoniazid resistant fabG1
Value: fabG1 is involved in the fatty acid synthesis pathway, acting in the first reduction step for mycolic acid. It is associated with isoniazid resistance.

Subject: isoniazid resistant inbR
Value: inbR is part of the transcriptional factor family TetR. It acts as a repressor to regulate efflux pumps involved in antibiotic resistance.

Subject: antibiotic resistant mshA
Value: mutations that occur in the mshA gene resulting in the inability for antibiotic to activate.

Subject: isoniazid resistant mshA
Value: mshA is a glycosyltransferase and is involved in the first step of mycothiol biosynthesis. This is a step that is required for growth in mycobacterium tuberculosis. Resistance has been shown in the gene to isoniazid.

Subject: isoniazid resistant mshB
Value: mshB is a deacetylase that is involved in the second step of mycothiol synthesis. GlcNAc-Ins is deacetylated by MshB to produce GlcN-Ins.

Subject: isoniazid resistant mymA
Value: mymA is an operon that begins at Rv3083 and ends at Rv3089 and is required for maintaining the appropriate mycolic acid composition and permeability of the envelope on its exposure to acidic pH. It has shown to be resistant to isoniazid.

Subject: antibiotic resistant nat
Value: mutations that occur in nat that inactivate antibiotic functioning and contribute to antibiotic resistance.

Subject: isoniazid resistant nudC
Value: nudC is a NADH pyrophosphatase that is involved in nicotinate and nicotinamide metabolism. Mutations that occur on the nudC gene resulting in the inability for isoniazid to function.

Subject: isoniazid resistant sigI
Value: a sigma factor that acts as an initiation factor that promotes attachment of the RNA polymerase to specific initiation sites and then is released. Transcriptional analyses indicate that katG is also regulated by the sigma factor sigl and indicate resistance to isoniaizd.

Subject: Mycobacterium tuberculosis eccB5 conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
Value: eccB5 is a transmembrane protein within the ESX-5 secretion system complex. The complex is critical for mycobacterium viability and virulence in the host cell and mutations contribute to a decreased uptake of antibiotic in the outer membrane.

Subject: Mycobacterium tuberculosis eccC5 conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones
Value: eccC5 is a membrane-bound ATPase within the ESX-5 secretion system complex. The complex is critical for mycobacterium viability and virulence in the host cell and mutations contribute to a decreased uptake of antibiotic in the outer membrane.

Subject: cycloserine resistant ddlA
Value: ddlA catalyzes the ATP-driven ligation of two D-alanine molecules to form the D-alanyl-D-alanine dipeptide, key in forming the cell wall. Cycloserine has a similar structure to d-alanine and inhibits the growth of the cell wall

Subject: cycloserine resistant ald
Value: ald plays a role in cell wall synthesis as L-alanine is an important constituent of the peptidoglycan layer. Resistance due to mutations in ald can cause cycloserine to not function.

Subject: Ethionamide resistant Rv0565c
Value: mycobacterial monoxygenase has been shown to confer resistance to ethionamide in recent literature

Subject: Neisseria gonorrhoeae rpld
Value: rpld encodes for the 50S L4 ribosomal protein, is a macrolide resistance protein identified in Neisseria gonorrhoeae.

Subject: antibiotic resistant ponA1
Value: a probable bifunctional penicillin-binding protein that is involved in the final stages of peptidoglycan synthesis. It has been shown to cause resistance to antibiotics.

Subject: streptomycin resistant whib7
Value: a protein involved in transcriptional mechanisms. Mutations in the gene can cause resistance to streptomycin.

Subject: kanamycin resistant whib7
Value: a protein involved in transcriptional mechanisms. Mutations in the gene can cause resistance to kanamycin.

Subject: rifampicin resistant rpoC
Value: rpoC catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA and mutations confer resistance to rifampicin

Subject: rifampicin resistant rpoA
Value: rpoA catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA and mutations confer resistance to rifampicin

Subject: IDC-1
Value: blaIDC-1 is an IDC class C beta-lactamase and an integron cephalosprinase

Subject: IDC-2
Value: blaIDC-1 is an IDC class C beta-lactamase and an integron cephalosprinase

Subject: cfr(D)
Value: cfr(D) is found in Enterococcus faecium. It confers resistance to vancomycin, teicoplanin, and linezolid.

Subject: cfr(E) Group
Value: cfr(E) is a cfr-like gene described by (Stojkovic et al, 2019). It is found on transposon Tn6218 and found in Clostridioides difficile.

Subject: cfr(E)
Value: cfr(E) is a cfr-like gene found in Clostridioides difficile isolate DF11. It confers resistance to antibiotics targeting to the 23s rRNA through hypermethylation of nucleotide A2503.

Subject: mlaF
Value: mlaF from the mla system is a gene proposed to play a part in the transport of phospholipids to the outer membrane. Insertions in mlaF are shown to confer resistance to linezolid.

Subject: mlaD
Value: mlaD from the mla system is a gene proposed to play a part in the transport of phospholipids to the outer membrane. Insertions in mlaD are shown to confer resistance to linezolid.

Subject: cmlA9
Value: cmlA9 is a Major Facilitator Superfamily efflux gene that is found in Salmonella enterica.

Subject: eptB
Value: eptB is a phosphoethanolamine transferase. It confers resistance to peptide antibiotics.

Subject: Intrinsic peptide antibiotic resistant Lps
Value: lpsB is involved in lipopolysaccharide synthesis. It provides intrinsic resistance to colistin and other peptide antibiotics such as polymyxins.

Subject: cprR
Value: cprR is one part of a two-component regulatory system. It with its counterpart cprS induce the Arn operon to confer resistance to peptide antibiotics.

Subject: cprS
Value: cprS is part of a two-component regulatory system that, with its counterpart cprR, induces the Arn operon in the presence of cationic peptides to confer resistance.

Subject: cprRS
Value: cprRS is a two-component regulatory system. In the presence of cationic peptides, it induces the Arn operon to confer resistance.

Subject: parRS
Value: parRS is a two-component sensor that mediates MexXY/OprM and porin OprD to confer resistance to polycationic antibiotics. It has multiple mechanisms of resistance such as LPS modification, efflux mediation and reduced porin pathway.

Subject: rsmA
Value: rsmA is a gene that regulates virulence of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. However, its negative effect on MexEF-OprN overexpression has been noted to confer resistance to various antibiotics. It's Escherichia coli homolog is csrA.

Subject: dfrA31
Value: dfrA31 is an antibiotic resistance dihydrofolate reductase from an integron found from Vibrio cholerae.

Subject: msrF
Value: msrF is an ABC-F binding cassette ribosomal protection protein. It confers resistance to macrolide antibiotics.

Subject: msrH
Value: msrH is a ABC-F binding cassette ribosomal protection protein. It confers resistance to macrolide antibiotics.

Subject: mef(D)
Value: mef(D) is a major facilitator superfamily efflux pump protein. It works together with the msr proteins to confer resistance to macrolide antibiotics.

Subject: lsa(D)
Value: lsa(D) is an ABC-F subfamily protein expressed in Lactococcus garvieae. It confers resistance to Streptogramins A, Pleuromutilins and Lincosamides.

Subject: dfrA35
Value: dfrA35 is a trimethoprim resistant dihydrofolate reductase gene found in the lncC plasmid pEc158 from E.coli.

Subject: diazabicyclooctanes ANT3310
Value: beta-lactamase inhibitor in the diazabicyclooctanes family

Subject: N,N'-bis(2-pyridylmethyl)-ethylenediamine
Value: polypyrimidine ligand as a metallo-beta-lactamase inhibitor

Subject: N,N,N'-tris(2-pyridylmethyl)-ethylenediamine
Value: polypyrimidine ligand derivative

Subject: N,N'-bis(2-pyridylmethyl)-ethylenediamine-N-acetic acid (N,N,N'-tris(2-pyridylmethyl)-ethylenediamine-N'-acetic acid
Value: polypyrimidine derivative

Subject: SHV-205
Value: a beta-lactamase gene found in Klebsiella pneumoniae. Directly submitted to NCBI without publication on 07-Nov-2018

Subject: SHV-208
Value: beta-lactamase gene from Klebsiella pneumoniae. Directly added to NCBI without publication on 07-NOV-2018

Subject: SHV-226
